Subject: Re: [T2] Re: No power at injectors ...

I recently had similar symptoms and had missed the line from the
ignition to the S15 coil connection. If someone turns the key to the run
position while you are at the back, you will hear the relay engage
(click) if this wire is connected.

If you have the Bentley, the troubleshooting steps at the double relay
were useful.

jack


On (05/02/05 08:12), Greg Potts penned:

> Sounds like a problem with the double relay or your wiring harness. It 
> could also be the ignition switch... do you lose ALL power when you 
> turn the key, or just power at the injectors? If you lose ALL power, 
> then the problem is at the ignition. Otherwise it's more likely to be 
> an issue with the double relay.

